column1: Reading instructions for the list of exchange places 2023 - 2024
Please note that numbers are subject to change. Student Exchange Services are not obliged to fill all places if there are no suitable candidates.
*) Please note that some Australian universities may require students to take TOEFL/IELTS language test if high school certificate does not fulfil the requirements (please see above).
If you are applying for the fall term to destination which requires a official language test score, the score needs to be available already during Aalto application round, Feb 23rd at the latest.

If you are applying to University of Southern California, Marshall School of Business (fall and spring), the offcial language test score needs to be available already during Aalto application round, Feb 23rd at the latest.
Language of instruction: for example Ger, (Eng) means that there are some courses in English, but most of the courses are in German.
Level of Studies: UG = undergraduate (kandidaattitaso)  G = graduate (maisteritaso). G (MBA) means that graduate students go to MBA program at the host university.
Please choose your preferred host university according to your level of studies.
Term structure: sem = semester  tri = trimester
Fall term and spring term: Please check the exact dates from the web page of each university.
Links to the web pages of the universities can be found from Exchange Finder
